title: Art Institute of Chicago Façade Ornament
description:
Ornament developed from Edward Kemeys’ Lions, 1893 and main entrance, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

This one-of-a-kind collectible honors our iconic guardian Lions, 1893 by Edward Kemeys (American, 1843-1907), which have stood at the Michigan Avenue entrance since the building’s inaugural year. Enjoy the intricate detail of architecture, finely etched on stainless steel. Made in the USA.

  • Dimensions: 3 x 2 ½ x .5 in.
  • Box dimensions: 4 x 4 x 1.25 in.
  • Materials: Stainless steel with silver finish & patina finish.
  • Weight: 3 oz.
